      • arcadeDrive

        public void arcadeDrive(double x,
                        double y,
                        double angle)
        Takes in x, y, and an angle to produce speeds for left and right gearboxes.

        Parameters:
        x - The x component to drive (Positive is right; Negative is left).
        y - The y component to drive (Positive is up; Negative is down).
        angle - The angle to drive (Positive is counterclockwise; Negative is clockwise).

      • jArcadeDrive

        Changes the inputs from the joystick to work with arcadeDrive.

        Parameters:
        x - The x component of the joystick.
        y - The y component of the joystick.
        twist - The twist component of the joystick.
